  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Peace and Ecological Spirituality Training for Community Leaders Following the Peace Agreements</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2016, after five decades of civil war, the Government of Colombia and the major guerrilla movement &#x2013; the FARC &#x2013; reached the Final Agreement, after a peace process that had been underway in Havana since 2012. Civil society in general, and the pastoral and development work of the Church in particular, played a key part in building a durable peace through work at grassroots and national level.

Since the Peace Accord has been ratified, the challenge is to take forward the peace-building process at the national level into the regions of the country where the war has been raging.  This present project seeks to prepare the country and the general population for the long and difficult process of peace-building and reconciliation within the communities. This will be developed through working with leaders who are trained and experienced in reconciliation processes and in sustainable development, bringing together a spirituality of peace along with the capacity of rebuilding the country at a regional level.  The project is based on the premise that the humanitarian crisis in Colombia is first and foremost a spiritual crisis, and a developmental crisis, because the country has been wounded by war and by the destruction of its natural resources, forests and waterways as a result of coca production for the drugs trade, illegal mining and major extractive exploitation of minerals and agro-industry.</narrative>
  </description>
